main event: A GCA Technician spotted a round object while working on an antenna on Coronado Island, California, in November 1956.
interesting points: The object was white and red,The observation lasted for 28 minutes,The technician reported that the object seemed to be intercepted by 2 aircraft,The object was initially spotted while working on ground radar,The conclusion suggested it might be a weather balloon.
sighted object: one round white and red object
